      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAST HARD COPY (12) was terrific when runner-up in a strong line-up in last week's Group 2 4YO Classic. That gave him placings in all three starts since a spell so his hoof is on the till. Draws on the back row but is peaking now and looks well placed. SUGAR SHAKE (1) drew very wide and worked last start so was far from disgraced when midfield. Had been runner-up in his other three starts this time in and is much better served by the ace draw. ROX THE WORLD (2) is another heading the right way, placing in his last three outings at this circuit and distance. Had wide or second row barriers in each of those so should get his chance from a more favourable draw. VINITA ROSE NZ (11) was fourth last start at Listed level and had good form prior, winning two back at this circuit and distance. Respect.",
